' FEC-GE Workflow (PlantUML)
' =========================
' Diagram 1: Full run from first generation to end (sampling once, then generation loop with FEC).
' Diagram 2: Per-individual evaluation showing how sampling feeds the cache and hits give speedup.
' Render: use PlantUML (jar, VS Code extension, or https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/uml/).

@startuml FEC_GE_One_Run_Workflow
title FEC-GE: One Run from First Generation to End

start
:Load dataset;
:Train and test split;
:Initialise empty FEC cache;

:Choose sampling method and fraction;
:Apply sampling to get centroid points;
note right: Sample used only for cache keys
:Store centroid data for cache key;

:Create initial population gen 0;
:generation = 0;

while (more generations)
  :generation = generation + 1;
  :For each individual in population;

  if (test set evaluation) then (yes)
    :Evaluate on test data;
    :Return test fitness;
  else (no)
    :Build fingerprint from phenotype on sample;
    if (fingerprint in cache) then (yes)
      :Return cached fitness;
      note right: Speedup
    else (no)
      :Evaluate on full training set;
      :Compute and store fitness in cache;
      :Return fitness;
    endif
  endif

  :Assign fitness;
  :Selection crossover mutation;
  :Replace population;
  :Record stats;
endwhile

:Return best individual;
:Return cache statistics;
stop

@enduml

' =============================================================================
' Diagram 2: Per-individual evaluation flow (cache + sampling → speedup)
' =============================================================================

@startuml FEC_GE_Evaluate_One_Individual
!theme plain
title Evaluate one individual (training)\nHow sampling feeds the cache and leads to speedup

skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

rectangle "**Inputs**" as inputs #F5F5F5 {
  (individual\nphenotype) as ind
  (full training data\nX_train, y_train) as full
  (sampled data\ncentroid_X, centroid_y) as sample
}

rectangle "**FEC evaluation**" as fec #E8F5E9 {
  (Build fingerprint) as build
  (Cache lookup) as lookup
  (Return cached fitness) as hit
  (Evaluate on FULL training set) as miss_eval
  (Store fitness in cache) as store
  (Return fitness_full) as miss_ret
}

inputs -[hidden]right- fec

ind --> build
sample --> build
note right of build
  **Sampling method** (k-means, farthest-point,
  stratified, …) chose which rows of X_train
  form **centroid_X**. We run phenotype on
  **this sample only** to get behavior key.
end note

build --> lookup : fingerprint =\nhash(behavior on sample)

lookup --> hit : **HIT**\n(fingerprint seen before)
lookup --> miss_eval : **MISS**\n(new fingerprint)

full --> miss_eval

hit --> (Speedup:\nno full eval)
miss_eval --> store : fitness_full
store --> miss_ret
miss_ret --> (Full eval done;\nstored for future hits)

@enduml

